Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.38,0:00:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to JW Broadcasting! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.99,0:00:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,On our program for this month, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.22,0:00:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ll hear the experience \Nof Brother Jim Brown. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:10.86,0:00:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He studied the Bible with Jehovah’s Witnesses \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.76,0:00:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,off and on for 30 years! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.07,0:00:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What motivated him to make changes \Nand dedicate his life to Jehovah? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.97,0:00:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,When serious problems arise in marriage, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.91,0:00:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,how will Bible principles help you? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.81,0:00:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The candid and heartfelt interviews \Nwith these couples \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.31,0:00:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,will show how the Bible \Nsaved their marriages. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.68,0:00:38.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s important for youths to develop \Ngood spiritual habits early. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.49,0:00:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,How can teenagers get the most \Nout of their daily Bible reading? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.96,0:00:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a lot to look forward to \Non the April 2018 edition \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.96,0:00:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of JW Broadcasting. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.52,0:01:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,As God’s Word touches \Nthe heart of a Bible student, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.59,0:01:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,they may need to make significant changes \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.22,0:01:16.49,Default,,0,0,0,,to live by Jehovah’s standards. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.49,0:01:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We start our program with just such a story. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.03,0:01:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Meet Jim Brown, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.13,0:01:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,a brother from Key Largo, Florida, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.27,0:01:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,in the United States. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.27,0:01:28.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Before becoming one of Jehovah’s Witnesses, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.67,0:01:32.58,Default,,0,0,0,,he was on a dangerous path \Nof vice and violence. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.58,0:01:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What changes did he have to make \Non the road to true worship? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.75,0:01:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m 53 years old.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.95,0:01:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I was known as a troublemaker.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.69,0:01:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I was fighting in the bars.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.76,0:01:53.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It comes to a point to where\Nyou begin to enjoy it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.43,0:01:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,He was flat-out scary.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.83,0:01:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,He was a very mean and violent man,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.94,0:02:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,so everybody\Nkind of kept their distance from him.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.14,0:02:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,My language was detestable.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.11,0:02:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I would make grown men blush\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.15,0:02:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,by the things that I would say\Nand things that I would do.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.95,0:02:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I was involved with some bikers,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.95,0:02:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and they were trying to prospect me\Ninto getting into their club.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.86,0:02:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Things were escalating.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.22,0:02:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We got married very young,\Nand we were 17.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.20,0:02:27.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And we had my oldest daughter.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.56,0:02:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I was the mom,\Nand he lived a life\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.97,0:02:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of being out with his friends\Nand partying.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.57,0:02:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,About that time, my wife started studying\Nthe Bible with Jehovah’s Witnesses. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.24,0:02:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a big change for her, \Nbut she explained the reasoning behind it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.08,0:02:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn’t argue with it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.68,0:02:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,She talked me into studying.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.38,0:02:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I studied from 20 years old to 30.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.16,0:02:53.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I had always seen it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.86,0:02:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I had always seen that it was good.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.33,0:02:57.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew that this was where I needed to be.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.16,0:03:01.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Somehow, I just could never break free\Nof the person that I was.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.03,0:03:03.10,Default,,0,0,0,,My mom always raised us in the truth, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.10,0:03:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,growing up, and that’s what we knew. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.07,0:03:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So, then, to see my dad, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.44,0:03:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,where he was so different\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.91,0:03:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,but yet believed it to be the truth, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.91,0:03:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and then to see that his lifestyle \Ndidn’t do him any good \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.78,0:03:18.45,Default,,0,0,0,,was kind of a good example\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.45,0:03:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of a bad example, if that makes sense.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.09,0:03:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I was afraid of the change.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.12,0:03:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,People accepted me for who I was,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.12,0:03:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,being the tough guy, being Jimmy Brown.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.73,0:03:34.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The scripture comes to mind:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.20,0:03:37.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“I planted, Apollos watered,\Nbut God kept making it grow.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.23,0:03:39.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Many brothers have studied with Jim\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.57,0:03:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,from time to time over the years.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.91,0:03:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I just happened to be the one\Nat the time in his life\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.81,0:03:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,when he was taking the truth\Nand running with it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.15,0:03:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to be a better person.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.38,0:03:56.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I truly knew that this was just\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.29,0:03:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,not the way of life that I wanted anymore.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.79,0:04:02.93,Default,,0,0,0,,He changed his friends;\Nhe changed his life;\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.93,0:04:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,he changed his dress and grooming; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.93,0:04:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,he changed his speech patterns;\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.46,0:04:10.43,Default,,0,0,0,,he changed the way he was a grandfather; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.43,0:04:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,he changed the way he was a father;\Nhe changed the way he was a husband.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.90,0:04:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything changed about him.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.11,0:04:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew the work that Witnesses do\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.11,0:04:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,—going out door to door talking to people. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.11,0:04:23.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought I could never do that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.68,0:04:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa! \NMe, going door to door? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.35,0:04:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m going to run into people that I know, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.85,0:04:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that I drank with for years and years. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.45,0:04:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,How can I face them now? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.29,0:04:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I had always told my wife, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.33,0:04:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,“It would be much easier for me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.33,0:04:39.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to become a Witness if I didn’t live here.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.96,0:04:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But how wrong I was\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.83,0:04:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,because what a witness my changes have been\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.64,0:04:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to so many people in town.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.04,0:04:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,One of my favorite things to do\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.18,0:04:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,is bridge witnessing with my granddaughter.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.05,0:05:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,People are fishing on the bridge\N—some have been there all night.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.52,0:05:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I even have return visits that I do\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.55,0:05:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,because people regularly\Ncome down on the weekend\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.65,0:05:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,to fish on the bridges.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.66,0:05:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I seize every opportunity.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.69,0:05:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,My kids laugh at me.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.66,0:05:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,He’ll witness to anybody, anytime, anywhere.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.36,0:05:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You’ll see some raggedy-taggedy,\Nold, rough guy\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.17,0:05:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,that he knew\Nand brought to the Kingdom Hall.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.70,0:05:21.70,Default,,0,0,0,,In a few weeks,\Nhe’s got a new suit on,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.70,0:05:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,got a haircut,\Nclean-shaven, and just—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.51,0:05:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the effect he has on the people\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.04,0:05:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that he comes in contact with.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.15,0:05:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I love life now.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.15,0:05:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I have true friends.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.15,0:05:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that I have hope for the future.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.75,0:05:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah has seen something in me,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.36,0:05:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and he’s brought it to light\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.36,0:05:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,that I am a good person.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.03,0:05:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I can be a good human being;\NI can help other people;\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.53,0:05:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I can be loved by Him.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.94,0:05:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s priceless.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.08,0:06:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you a Bible student who is undecided \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.92,0:06:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,on whether to “commit your way to Jehovah”? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.92,0:06:13.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Take note of the trust and confidence \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.16,0:06:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Brown showed \Nin dedicating his life to God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.46,0:06:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Be assured that Jehovah \Nwill guide and care for us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.26,0:06:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,if we give him the opportunity. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.83,0:06:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Brown now enjoys the blessing \Nof living under Jehovah’s protection, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.64,0:06:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,serving as a ministerial servant \Nand regular pioneer. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.37,0:06:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You too can experience \NJehovah’s spiritual protection, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.61,0:06:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,as we’ll learn throughout our program. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.92,0:06:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The theme of our broadcast \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.62,0:06:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,is a very comforting one: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.75,0:06:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,“Being ‘Securely Wrapped \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.95,0:06:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in the Bag of Life With Jehovah.’” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.42,0:06:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps the thought \Nof being securely wrapped \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.83,0:06:53.70,Default,,0,0,0,,makes us think of a safely swaddled baby \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.70,0:06:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,or of being enveloped \Nin a warm blanket on a cold night. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.10,0:07:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Bible, these words \Nwere uttered by the woman Abigail \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.74,0:07:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,to Jehovah’s servant David. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.97,0:07:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,To understand the meaning of the words \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.21,0:07:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and their importance today, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.21,0:07:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s review the context \Nof 1 Samuel chapter 25. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.48,0:07:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,David and 600 of his men \N were dwelling as fugitives. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.35,0:07:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,They eventually encountered men \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.35,0:07:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,who worked as shepherds \Nfor Abigail’s husband, Nabal. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.72,0:07:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,David and his men began \Nto help guard Nabal’s flocks \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.73,0:07:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and serve as “a protective wall” \Nfor Nabal’s flocks and servants \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.37,0:07:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,against thieves and invaders \Nwho roamed through the wilderness. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.70,0:07:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It was likely challenging \Nto find enough food for 600 soldiers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.24,0:07:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,so David decided to send ten of his men \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.71,0:07:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,to kindly ask Nabal for food \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.31,0:07:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,in repayment for the services \Nthat they had performed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.55,0:07:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But at 1 Samuel 25:10, 11, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.96,0:07:55.96,Default,,0,0,0,,note Nabal’s reply: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.96,0:07:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“Nabal answered David’s servants: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.00,0:08:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Who is David, and who is the son of Jesse? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.37,0:08:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Nowadays many servants \Nare breaking away from their masters. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.77,0:08:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Do I have to take my bread and my water \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.51,0:08:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘and the meat \Nthat I butchered for my shearers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.14,0:08:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and give it to men who come \Nfrom who knows where?’” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.08,0:08:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,This was not the response that David \Nand his men were expecting to hear. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.09,0:08:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible describes Nabal \Nas a very harsh, worthless man, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.09,0:08:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and this is certainly evidenced by his reply. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.53,0:08:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,“He screamed insults” \Nat the messengers and ridiculed David, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.70,0:08:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,comparing him to a runaway servant. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.10,0:08:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So David decided \Nto take matters into his own hands \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.97,0:08:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and resolve the situation \Nthe way many people today might \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.88,0:08:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,—by fighting. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.08,0:08:51.08,Default,,0,0,0,,In verse 13, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.08,0:08:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,he has 400 of his men \Nprepare themselves for battle, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.22,0:08:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,with one mission\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.25,0:08:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,—to wipe out every male \Nin Nabal’s household. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.62,0:09:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, word got back to Abigail \Nabout what her husband had done. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.19,0:09:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Without telling Nabal, \Nshe gathered an abundance of food \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.33,0:09:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and went out to meet David. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.67,0:09:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,When she met up with him, \Nshe poured out her heart at length, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.47,0:09:17.07,Default,,0,0,0,,asking David to forgive her personally \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.07,0:09:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and making a powerful plea for mercy \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.28,0:09:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,on behalf of her husband and her household. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.55,0:09:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,She acknowledged that Nabal \Nwas a foolish and senseless man, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.48,0:09:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,so she urged David not to take any action \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.39,0:09:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that might bring bloodguilt upon him \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.52,0:09:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,or cause him to be affected \Nby a troubled conscience. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.52,0:09:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,As Abigail concluded her appeal to David, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.83,0:09:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,notice what she tells him in verse 29, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.73,0:09:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,the theme of our discussion: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.87,0:09:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“When someone rises up \Nto pursue you and seeks your life, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.37,0:09:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,“the life of my lord will be wrapped securely \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.54,0:09:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“in the bag of life with Jehovah your God, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.51,0:09:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,“but the lives of your enemies \N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.51,0:10:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,he will hurl away like stones from a sling.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.59,0:10:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as we might wrap up something valuable \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.59,0:10:08.09,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to protect and preserve it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.09,0:10:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Abigail was telling David \Nthat that is how his life \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.23,0:10:13.40,Default,,0,0,0,,would be in Jehovah’s hands. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.40,0:10:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah would protect and preserve \NDavid’s life from his enemies \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.37,0:10:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,as long as he did not seek \Nto save himself by personal efforts \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.67,0:10:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,but waited on Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.87,0:10:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,trusting in the One to whom he owed his life.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.54,0:10:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,What lessons can we learn from this account? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.42,0:10:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,As David saw, his relationship \Nwith Jehovah was a protection. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.99,0:10:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,In verse 32, he acknowledges \Nthat God had sent Abigail with the warning. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.83,0:10:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We learn \Nthat Jehovah’s spiritual protection for us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.43,0:10:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is related to the quality \Nof our relationship with him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.00,0:10:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s why the Bible tells us at James 4:8: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.67,0:10:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“Draw close to God, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.34,0:11:02.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and he will draw close to you.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.41,0:11:05.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah invites us to draw near to him \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.41,0:11:10.12,Default,,0,0,0,,because he wants to receive us \Ninto his favor as his friends. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.12,0:11:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,When we dedicate our lives \Nand vow to serve him unconditionally, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.39,0:11:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,we gain an approved standing with him; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.73,0:11:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re figuratively put in that “bag of life.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.16,0:11:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we work to develop \Na close personal relationship with him, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.50,0:11:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,then we can experience \NJehovah’s friendship and protection. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.77,0:11:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We would never want \Nto restrict Jehovah’s protection \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.64,0:11:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,by not looking to him for guidance \Nor relying on our own thinking. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.05,0:11:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, can we think of areas or situations \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.15,0:11:43.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that might require us to wait on Jehovah? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.45,0:11:48.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps we’re experiencing \Nliteral opposition at work or at school. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.49,0:11:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Like Abigail, we might face the challenge \Nof living with a difficult marriage mate. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.20,0:11:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe we’re battling a health issue \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.20,0:11:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and loyalty is needed \Nregarding our medical choices. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.77,0:12:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Or it may be that we live in a country \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.77,0:12:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,where we cannot preach freely \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.87,0:12:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,or that we face opposition for our beliefs. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.88,0:12:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, it could be any number of situations. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.38,0:12:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But it is our response\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.78,0:12:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,—the way we handle the situation—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.32,0:12:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that indicates how much \Nwe are allowing Jehovah to help us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.32,0:12:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Do we trust him enough \Nthat we can leave the matter in his hands \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.33,0:12:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and see how he works \Nthings out in our behalf? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.37,0:12:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to manifest \NChristian qualities in order to do that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.10,0:12:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about what qualities displayed \Nby Abigail and David impress you most. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.68,0:12:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Two that come to mind \Nare patience and reasonableness. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.08,0:12:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Patience is closely connected with endurance \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.85,0:12:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,and enables one to put up \Nwith difficult circumstances \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.45,0:12:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,while maintaining a positive attitude. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.82,0:12:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Reasonableness describes \Na person who is fair, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.33,0:13:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,considerate, willing to yield to others. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.23,0:13:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,How well this describes Abigail! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.67,0:13:09.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It must have been quite a challenge \Nto live with someone like Nabal. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.31,0:13:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But nowhere do we read \Nthat she was ever disrespectful of him \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.51,0:13:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,or that she belittled him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.51,0:13:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Even when she referred to him \Nas senseless in verse 25, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.75,0:13:23.25,Default,,0,0,0,,from Jehovah’s standpoint, \Nher comments were proper \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.25,0:13:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,because Nabal’s actions \Nput his entire household in danger. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.26,0:13:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,How about David? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.36,0:13:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,He was in a position of authority, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.53,0:13:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,but he showed great patience \Nand reasonableness in listening to Abigail \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.20,0:13:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and having the good sense \Nto know that she was right. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.67,0:13:43.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s not always easy to do \Nin the heat of the moment \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.64,0:13:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,or when we’re upset. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.11,0:13:48.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps you recall that at our \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.11,0:13:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“Don’t Give Up!” \NRegional Convention last year, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.91,0:13:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,when discussing 2 Peter 1:5-8, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.98,0:13:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,we learned a nice formula \Nthat can help us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.62,0:14:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to cultivate and strengthen \NChristian qualities. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.19,0:14:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We were encouraged to study them, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.66,0:14:07.06,Default,,0,0,0,,meditate on them, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.06,0:14:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and put them into practice. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.63,0:14:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,If we apply this formula \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.63,0:14:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,with the qualities \Nof patience and reasonableness, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.34,0:14:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,it can help us to endure \Nour trials successfully. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.04,0:14:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And we’re confident \Nthat Jehovah will supply us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.61,0:14:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,with whatever power we need \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.05,0:14:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,so that we will not tire out \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.35,0:14:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,as we continue to endure \Nand put our trust in him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.52,0:14:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition to developing these qualities, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.66,0:14:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,something else that can help us \Nis our spiritual routine. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.43,0:14:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Our consistent routine \Nof study, meeting attendance, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.63,0:14:44.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and the ministry will help us remain busy, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.17,0:14:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,stay active, and make good decisions. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.17,0:14:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll have no time \Nto become curious or occupied \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.67,0:14:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,with the things this world has to offer. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.11,0:14:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s good to remember \Nthe people during the days of Haggai. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.88,0:15:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,When the Jews lost their focus \Nand started neglecting Jehovah’s temple, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.89,0:15:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,they lost his blessing \Nand protection spiritually. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.29,0:15:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And what was the result? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.89,0:15:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, notice how Haggai draws our attention \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.66,0:15:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,to a different type of “bag” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.20,0:15:20.44,Default,,0,0,0,,at Haggai 1:6: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.44,0:15:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,“You have sown much seed, \Nbut you harvest little. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.47,0:15:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,“You eat, but it is not to satisfaction. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.41,0:15:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,“You drink, but you do not drink your fill. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.05,0:15:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“You put on clothing, but no one gets warm. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.69,0:15:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,“The one who hires himself out puts his wages \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.19,0:15:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,in a bag full of holes.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.89,0:15:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The Jews sowed seed \Nbut had a meager harvest. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.33,0:15:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,They lacked enough food \Nto satisfy their needs. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.53,0:15:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They were unable to clothe \Nthemselves with warm garments. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.00,0:15:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Because Jehovah withheld his blessings, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.24,0:16:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Haggai rightly compared them to a man \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.24,0:16:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,who “puts his wages in a bag full of holes.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.65,0:16:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Imagine the disappointment \Nof discovering that hard-earned wages \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.05,0:16:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,had gradually disappeared \Nthrough a leaking bag! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.92,0:16:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, \Nour focus is not material prosperity, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.86,0:16:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,because, whether we have \Nan abundance of material things or not, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.46,0:16:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,if we fail to receive Jehovah’s blessing, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.97,0:16:28.37,Default,,0,0,0,,our spirituality is jeopardized. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.37,0:16:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So we must be determined \Nnever to lose our focus \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.18,0:16:37.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and keep Jehovah \Nin the forefront of our lives.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.61,0:16:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,When we examine the life of David, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.52,0:16:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s evident that he enjoyed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.62,0:16:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,a preserved and protected \Nrelationship with God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.69,0:16:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,When you read the book of Psalms, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.06,0:16:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,take note of how David \Ndescribes Jehovah’s protective care \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.90,0:16:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,in Psalm 18, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.90,0:16:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Psalm 31, and Psalm 34 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.00,0:17:01.07,Default,,0,0,0,,as he went through distresses \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.07,0:17:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,—just beautiful accounts! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.94,0:17:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, did David always do \Neverything the right way? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.88,0:17:09.45,Default,,0,0,0,,No. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.45,0:17:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of his encounter with Nabal. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.78,0:17:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,While his angry reaction was understandable, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.05,0:17:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,his way of expressing it was not correct. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.95,0:17:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But David learned from his mistakes, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.92,0:17:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and each new trial that he went through \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.96,0:17:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,strengthened his relationship \Nwith Jehovah even more. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.76,0:17:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, \Nafter the ordeal with Nabal, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.57,0:17:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,a short time later, \NDavid married Abigail. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.04,0:17:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,They were still fugitives, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.07,0:17:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,but he found a king that befriended them, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.64,0:17:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and he gave David’s men \Nand family a land to dwell in. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.58,0:17:47.55,Default,,0,0,0,,One day, while all the men were away, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.55,0:17:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the Amalekites raided and burned the city \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.72,0:17:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and carried off all the men’s wives, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.32,0:17:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,children, and flocks. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.62,0:17:58.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Upon returning \Nand seeing what had happened, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.36,0:18:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,David and his men wept. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.33,0:18:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Grief quickly turned to bitterness, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.00,0:18:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and David’s men spoke of stoning him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.40,0:18:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,This was likely quite stressful for David. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.97,0:18:13.98,Default,,0,0,0,,He was concerned \Nfor the safety of his family, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.98,0:18:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and likely he was frustrated \Nthat his men had turned on him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.88,0:18:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe he felt disrespected again, \Nas he had with Nabal. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.82,0:18:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So how would he handle this situation? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.66,0:18:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We get a glimpse of David’s feelings \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.02,0:18:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,at 1 Samuel 30:6: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.36,0:18:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,“David was very distressed, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.47,0:18:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“because the men were talking of stoning him, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.34,0:18:43.01,Default,,0,0,0,,“for all the men had become very bitter \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.01,0:18:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,over the loss of their sons and daughters.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.21,0:18:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,But notice, \Nhow did David handle the situation? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.11,0:18:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The verse continues: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.68,0:18:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“But David strengthened himself \Nby Jehovah his God.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.72,0:19:02.22,Default,,0,0,0,,How did he do this? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.22,0:19:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Verse 8 says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.46,0:19:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,“David inquired of Jehovah.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.67,0:19:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,This time, David has \Na different thought process and response. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.34,0:19:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Immediately he remembers \Nto consult Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.37,0:19:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn’t this a nice reminder \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.38,0:19:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that when you and I are going \Nthrough difficult trials and situations, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.31,0:19:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,we want to immediately pray to Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.12,0:19:32.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and seek his direction \Nthrough the pages of his Word, the Bible? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.82,0:19:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This is essential \Nfor our spiritual protection. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.76,0:19:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So in review, \Nas we face difficult situations in life, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.77,0:19:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,may we look for opportunities \Nto show and develop our Christian qualities \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.44,0:19:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,—such as patience and reasonableness. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.67,0:19:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,These qualities show Jehovah \Nthat we want to be like him, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.48,0:19:58.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that we have \Nthe mental disposition of Christ, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.08,0:20:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and that we will allow Him \Nto guide us constantly. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.75,0:20:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, may we keep focused and busy \N“in the work of the Lord.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.56,0:20:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,By drawing close to Jehovah through prayer \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.53,0:20:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and engaging in spiritual activities, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.13,0:20:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,we make the best of our situation now. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.70,0:20:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But we will also find \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.70,0:20:21.97,Default,,0,0,0,,everlasting protection in Jehovah’s hands, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.97,0:20:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,safely swaddled \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.97,0:20:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and securely wrapped in his “bag of life”! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.51,0:20:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to rely on Jehovah’s guidance \Neven in the most severe trials. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.52,0:20:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s possible that you \Nmay face a life-threatening issue \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.92,0:20:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,where there’s no desirable option, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.42,0:20:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,but a decision is necessary. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.53,0:20:45.93,Default,,0,0,0,,In the following dramatization, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.93,0:20:49.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Emma is faced with a situation like this. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.40,0:20:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What will she do? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.40,0:20:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And how will God’s Word \Nhelp her to make a decision? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.07,0:21:01.38,Default,,0,0,0,,When Thomas and I first learned \NI was pregnant, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.38,0:21:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we were both really shocked. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.28,0:21:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But then we grew more and more excited. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.42,0:21:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And we were so thrilled when we saw \Nour little girl for the first time. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.20,0:21:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We really didn’t care \Nif it was a boy or a girl; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.80,0:21:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we just wanted the baby to be healthy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.12,0:21:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Unfortunately, our hopes \Nwere completely destroyed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.39,0:21:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,when the doctor told us \Nthat the baby would likely be born \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.63,0:21:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,with severe problems and could even die. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.84,0:22:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,My husband and his parents \Nare not Jehovah’s Witnesses, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.61,0:22:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but they do feel abortion is wrong. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.49,0:22:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, they thought that we should listen \Nto our doctor’s advice. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.19,0:22:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn’t believe this was happening. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.96,0:22:32.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I even questioned why Jehovah would allow it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.30,0:22:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I really felt it was more than I could bear. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.71,0:22:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Thomas asked me what I wanted to do, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.14,0:22:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and I told him \Nthat I could never have an abortion. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.88,0:22:47.95,Default,,0,0,0,,He agreed that normally it would be wrong \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.95,0:22:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but felt that in our situation \NGod would understand. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.69,0:22:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I was so overwhelmed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.89,0:23:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I was being pressured \Nto make a decision I knew was wrong \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.90,0:23:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but that everyone \Nwas telling me was best for my child. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.40,0:23:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I had never felt so alone. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.41,0:23:16.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I needed Jehovah more than ever, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.18,0:23:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,so I poured out my heart to him in prayer. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.56,0:23:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I did research. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.95,0:23:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I showed Thomas the scripture I had found. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.26,0:24:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“If men should struggle with each other \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.80,0:24:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“and they hurt a pregnant woman \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.60,0:24:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,“. . . if a fatality does occur, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.57,0:24:21.71,Default,,0,0,0,,then you must give life for life.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.71,0:24:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah views even the unintentional killing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.78,0:24:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,of an unborn child as a serious sin. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.82,0:24:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So how could we intentionally take \Nthe life of our child? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.56,0:24:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I made my decision clear to our doctor \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.27,0:24:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and to my in-laws. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.31,0:24:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a chance \Nthe diagnosis was incorrect, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.98,0:24:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and I’d love to say that’s what occurred; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.08,0:24:59.25,Default,,0,0,0,,but it did not. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.25,0:25:03.45,Default,,0,0,0,,My daughter Chloe only lived \Na few weeks after she was born, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.45,0:25:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,and losing her was the hardest thing \NI’ve ever had to endure. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.82,0:25:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jehovah gave me the courage \Nto explain my beliefs to my husband, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.96,0:25:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,my in-laws, and the medical staff, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.00,0:25:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and they all expressed admiration \Nfor my strong faith. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.03,0:25:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And I’ve never regretted the decision I made. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.77,0:25:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though Chloe only lived those few weeks, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.94,0:25:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m so grateful for the time I had with her. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.44,0:25:33.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I know Jehovah remembers \Nevery detail about her, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.45,0:25:37.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and he’ll give her back to me \Nin the resurrection in perfect health, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.95,0:25:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,because all life \Nis truly precious in his eyes. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.66,0:25:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Getting Jehovah’s thinking on a matter \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.66,0:25:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,should be the first thing \Nwe do when making decisions. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.54,0:25:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,This is especially true \Nwhen well-intentioned friends or family \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.57,0:26:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,offer advice that may conflict \Nwith Bible principles. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.31,0:26:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,As we weigh a variety of options, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.81,0:26:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,follow Emma’s good example \Nof consulting God’s Word \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.85,0:26:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and our Christian publications. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.95,0:26:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This will help us make decisions \Nthat bring honor to Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.52,0:26:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Emma’s Christian conduct \Nhelped her to navigate \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.69,0:26:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,a potentially divisive moment \Nin her marriage. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.30,0:26:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But unfortunately, \Nthis system of things and our imperfect flesh \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.13,0:26:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,can create extreme tension in a marriage. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.84,0:26:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Can the Bible save \Na marriage that’s in danger? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.57,0:26:36.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The following interviews, \Nwhile very frank, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.04,0:26:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,will show the exceeding value \Nof God’s own Word, the Bible, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.45,0:26:42.95,Default,,0,0,0,,to preserve that divine union. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.95,0:26:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Almost from the start of the marriage, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.12,0:26:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,it was not running smoothly, \Nto say the least. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.16,0:26:52.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We were fighting constantly. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.93,0:26:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the smallest things \Nwe would argue over, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.47,0:27:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and it would just get blown \Nout of proportion. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.57,0:27:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We couldn’t communicate \Nwithout it being an argument. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.47,0:27:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Steadily the arguments increased \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.01,0:27:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,in frequency and intensity. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.35,0:27:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And you think, ‘Well, I’m not happy here,’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:14.55,0:27:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and that’s when I threatened to leave. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.79,0:27:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes I felt \Nlike completely giving up on the marriage. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.46,0:27:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,There would be arguments \Nwhere you’d be packing the bags \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.46,0:27:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and saying you’d wished you’d never done it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.70,0:27:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And ultimately it would end in insults. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.10,0:27:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah was missing in our marriage, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.87,0:27:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and that was the essential part \Nof making our marriage work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.37,0:27:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,A brother and sister \Nthat we’d known for a long time \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.38,0:27:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,initially offered us a Bible study. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.98,0:27:45.91,Default,,0,0,0,,They invited us \Nto their Family Worship evening \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.91,0:27:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to have dinner \Nand to do The Watchtower with them, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.28,0:27:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,which we accepted. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.29,0:27:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The Family Worship arrangement helped \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.59,0:27:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,because it wasn’t just Bible principles \Nthat you read about, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.86,0:27:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,but we saw them being applied \Nin this couple’s life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.56,0:28:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And so all of a sudden, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.56,0:28:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I could see the cause and effect \Nof a Bible principle. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.03,0:28:09.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But the impact \Nthat it was having was tremendous \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.87,0:28:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,because we could see how to apply \Na Bible principle and make it work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.88,0:28:18.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it took a long time \Nbefore things got better, honestly, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.11,0:28:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,but the turning point \Nwas coming back to Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.25,0:28:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,There were many principles \Nthat all of a sudden \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.25,0:28:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,were like little light bulbs going off, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.89,0:28:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,such as Jesus at John 13:34 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.26,0:28:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,when he recommended his example. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.89,0:28:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Ephesians 5:33 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.80,0:28:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,eventually had an impact on me, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.83,0:28:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,because there were articles that pointed out \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.13,0:28:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,how important it is for a husband \Nto feel respected by his wife, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.04,0:28:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and I don’t think \NI’d ever really appreciated that before. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.84,0:28:48.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I just viewed it as a mechanical process: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.01,0:28:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s the head; \Nhe needs to have respect from his wife. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.51,0:28:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t recognize that it’s important \Nfor a husband to feel respected \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.88,0:29:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to be able to take on his role as head. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.42,0:29:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re so thankful \Nto Jehovah for his patience. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.93,0:29:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible principles were always there; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.13,0:29:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,we just weren’t making application of them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.13,0:29:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as we started to make application, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.17,0:29:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,our marriage did a complete turnaround. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.54,0:29:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Where we are now is totally different. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.17,0:29:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The relationship that we have \Nis what we wanted at the start \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:20.64,0:29:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,but didn’t know how to get. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:22.64,0:29:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s just that application \Nof Bible principles \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.65,0:29:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that has made it possible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.85,0:29:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We were 17, actually, when we met \Nand 20 when we got married. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.52,0:29:40.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Life was good for Tony and me; \Nwe were happy. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.43,0:29:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But then I got into another business \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.77,0:29:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that became the main focus in my life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.80,0:29:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It had quite a dramatic effect \Non our spirituality. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.24,0:29:54.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We went through a time \Nwhen we hardly saw each other, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.24,0:29:57.18,Default,,0,0,0,,so there was a great deal \Nof time that we spent apart. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.18,0:30:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Bible principles were ones \Nthat weren’t brought into our life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.18,0:30:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time, \NBible reading was out of the picture. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.62,0:30:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I started delving into viewing things \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.69,0:30:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that were really, really inappropriate. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.86,0:30:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it eventually happened \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.46,0:30:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,where I didn’t really care what I viewed, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.17,0:30:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and I didn’t think about the consequences \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.84,0:30:26.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and of the unhappiness that it would cause. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.54,0:30:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It made me feel very, extremely, unloved. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.48,0:30:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt very angry about his behavior. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.12,0:30:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt a lot of resentment \Ntowards him, a lot of bitterness. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.19,0:30:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We ended up in separation, to begin with. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.76,0:30:45.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I left Tony; I walked away from him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.23,0:30:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I walked away from the marriage, \Nwalked away from the business \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.36,0:30:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and, eventually, \Nended up unscripturally divorcing Tony. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.47,0:30:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The elders who were assisting me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.44,0:31:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,helped me to see exactly how Jehovah felt \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.08,0:31:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,about what I’d been doing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.08,0:31:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and where my relationship was with him, \Nand it was quite poor. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.72,0:31:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt that because of the betrayal \Nthat I had experienced, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.19,0:31:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I did not have a problem with my conscience \Nat all in going through the divorce. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.62,0:31:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It seemed the logical \Nand best way for me to go. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.39,0:31:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,With my Bible reading, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.76,0:31:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I got to see Amos 5:15. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.50,0:31:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It really had an effect on me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.50,0:31:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,because I needed to “hate what is bad, \Nand love what is good.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.74,0:31:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,One scripture that affected me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.74,0:31:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,was from Malachi \Nabout how Jehovah felt about divorce. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.54,0:31:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Altogether, it took us 15 years \Nbefore we got together again. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.85,0:31:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I was just enjoying \Na day out in the field midweek, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.95,0:31:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and I got home in mid-afternoon. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.99,0:31:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And all of a sudden, my mobile phone rang, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.76,0:31:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and I heard Rhonda’s voice. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.56,0:31:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,What a delight it was \Nthat she was inviting me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.30,0:31:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,to accompany her \Nfor a cup of coffee somewhere \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.33,0:32:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to talk about things! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.64,0:32:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,If I hadn’t started \Nhaving a Scriptural intake \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.71,0:32:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and learning to love God’s Word, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.51,0:32:12.58,Default,,0,0,0,,my life wouldn’t have changed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.58,0:32:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Without the Bible, \NTony and I would not be together. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.98,0:32:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The marriage \Nwould never ever have reconciled. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.72,0:32:22.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We have become best friends, \Nso we really enjoy \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.32,0:32:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,being in each other’s company \Nand serving Jehovah together. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.16,0:32:29.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Our married life now has certainly benefited \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.06,0:32:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,by both of us seeing \Nhow beneficial the Scriptures are. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.77,0:32:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Tony and I are now very much a couple, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.94,0:32:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and so no matter what we deal with, \Nit’s us together. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.24,0:32:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,When situations like these arise, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.81,0:32:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s not just our marriage that’s affected. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.41,0:32:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Our relationship with Jehovah is on the line! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.85,0:32:51.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Our dear sister, for example, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.89,0:32:54.99,Default,,0,0,0,,reached an emotional point \Nwhere she felt the only solution \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.99,0:32:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,was an unscriptural divorce. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.59,0:33:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,As we make our decisions in marriage, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.33,0:33:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s feelings on the subject, \Nfound at Malachi 2:16, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.87,0:33:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,should be carefully considered: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.67,0:33:10.81,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘For I hate divorce,’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.81,0:33:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,says Jehovah the God of Israel.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.04,0:33:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If you find your marital peace is threatened, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.88,0:33:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,review articles like the one \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.91,0:33:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in the May 15, 2012, study edition \Nof The Watchtower entitled \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.92,0:33:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“Take a Positive View \Nof a Strained Marriage.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.66,0:33:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It provides powerful counsel that can help \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.43,0:33:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to save and strengthen your marriage bond. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.53,0:33:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,In our program, we’ve seen a few ways \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.70,0:33:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that Satan will exert pressure on those \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.53,0:33:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,‘securely wrapped in the bag of life.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.27,0:33:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,True Christians \Ncourageously stand up to the Devil, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.34,0:33:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,never allowing him to pry us \Naway from Jehovah’s protection. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.51,0:33:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,At a recent Bethel morning worship, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.78,0:33:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother Mark Sanderson \Nof the Governing Body discussed 1 Peter 5:9 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.78,0:34:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and outlined how we take \Nour stand against Satan. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.29,0:34:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it possible to survive \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.83,0:34:07.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the attack of a roaring lion? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.20,0:34:08.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now, I did some \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.53,0:34:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,—just quick—checking \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.53,0:34:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,on various wildlife websites, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.43,0:34:13.67,Default,,0,0,0,,and here’s what they say. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.67,0:34:14.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Basically, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.67,0:34:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,they all give the same advice \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.40,0:34:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,if you’re being attacked by a lion. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.67,0:34:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,They say: “Hold your ground. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.28,0:34:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Never run or turn back.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.55,0:34:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, one website says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.42,0:34:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,“A lion can run 50 miles per hour (80 km/h). \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.79,0:34:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,“So stand still. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.92,0:34:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If you run, you will only die tired.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.16,0:34:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that’s true. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.26,0:34:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,First Peter 5:9 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.53,0:34:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,gives us exactly the same advice. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.93,0:34:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It says: “Take your stand against him.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.21,0:34:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in this case \Nnot against a literal lion, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.58,0:34:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,but against that “roaring lion,” \NSatan the Devil, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.28,0:35:03.15,Default,,0,0,0,,who is seeking to devour \Nevery single one of us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.15,0:35:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Our ability to stand firm \Nwhen facing this lion \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.76,0:35:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,—to be able to oppose him, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.89,0:35:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,to refuse to be intimidated by him, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.29,0:35:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to refuse to run away or turn back— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.30,0:35:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,requires what the apostle Peter \Nnext mentions there in verse 9, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.94,0:35:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and Brother Crane \Nso nicely covered in his comment. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.94,0:35:28.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to: “Take [our] stand against him, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.54,0:35:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,firm in the faith.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.25,0:35:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,To be successful, \Nwe must have complete trust \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.52,0:35:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and complete confidence in Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.22,0:35:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now, in that regard, \Nlet’s look at an example \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.69,0:35:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,of someone in Bible times who had \Nthat kind of confidence in Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.16,0:35:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,This is in the days of King Jehoshaphat, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.70,0:35:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,when Judah was threatened \Nby the combined forces \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.14,0:35:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,, of Moab, Ammon, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.14,0:35:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,and the inhabitants \Nof the mountainous region of Seir. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.17,0:36:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Now let’s begin by opening our Bibles \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.91,0:36:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and reading 2 Chronicles 20:12. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.92,0:36:10.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So here Jehoshaphat is praying to Jehovah; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.72,0:36:14.52,Default,,0,0,0,,he’s pouring out his heart to him, \Nand see what he says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.52,0:36:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,“O our God, \Nwill you not execute judgment on them? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.53,0:36:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“For we are powerless before this large crowd \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.03,0:36:25.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“that is coming against us; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.03,0:36:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“and we do not know what we should do, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.34,0:36:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,but our eyes are toward you.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.34,0:36:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Jehoshaphat was facing the lion. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.31,0:36:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,He said to Jehovah: \N‘We don’t know what to do.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.35,0:36:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But Jehoshaphat had complete and total trust; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.35,0:36:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,he had firm faith in Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.19,0:36:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what did Jehovah \Ntell Jehoshaphat to do? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.49,0:36:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,See verse 17: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.20,0:36:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,“You will not need to fight this battle. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.47,0:36:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Take your position.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.57,0:37:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Does that sound familiar? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.57,0:37:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“Take your position, stand still, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.37,0:37:09.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“and see the salvation of Jehovah \Nin your behalf. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.34,0:37:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,“O Judah and Jerusalem, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.35,0:37:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“do not be afraid or be terrified. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.78,0:37:16.22,Default,,0,0,0,,“Tomorrow go out against them, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.22,0:37:19.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and Jehovah will be with you.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.25,0:37:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what did Jehovah tell them to do? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.02,0:37:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,He said: ‘Take a position \Nin opposition to that military force, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.89,0:37:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,‘stand firm, refuse to run away, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.50,0:37:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and see the salvation \Nthat will come from Jehovah.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.60,0:37:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in order to do that, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.60,0:37:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehoshaphat and the people with him \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.91,0:37:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,would need to have strong, firm, solid faith. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.28,0:37:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now, to help the people, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.28,0:37:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,look at what Jehoshaphat said to them \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.38,0:37:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,as they were getting ready for this battle. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.48,0:37:55.19,Default,,0,0,0,,In verse 20, you see, \Njust about the middle of the verse, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.19,0:37:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,it says: \N“Jehoshaphat stood up and said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.33,0:38:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Listen to me, O Judah \Nand you inhabitants of Jerusalem! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.80,0:38:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Put faith in Jehovah your God \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.57,0:38:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘so that you may be able to stand firm. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.14,0:38:12.77,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Put faith in his prophets, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.77,0:38:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and you will be successful.’” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.41,0:38:18.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that’s exactly what happened. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.78,0:38:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,See, with that kind of confidence in Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.08,0:38:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,with that firm trust in him, \Nwith that standing firm, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.35,0:38:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,what did Jehovah do? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.36,0:38:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, according to verses 22 and 23\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.12,0:38:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,—you’ll remember what happened—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.13,0:38:35.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the men of Ammon, Moab, \Nand the inhabitants \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.36,0:38:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,of the mountainous region of Seir, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.70,0:38:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,they all went to striking down one another. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.00,0:38:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And verse 23 says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:43.30,0:38:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,“And the Ammonites and the Moabites \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.57,0:38:49.31,Default,,0,0,0,,“turned against the inhabitants \Nof the mountainous region of Seir \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.31,0:38:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“to destroy and annihilate them; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.71,0:38:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,“and when they finished \Nwith the inhabitants of Seir, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.58,0:38:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,they helped to destroy one another.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.95,0:39:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, Jehovah had rewarded \Ntheir firm faith in him. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.96,0:39:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The weapons that had been formed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.23,0:39:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,against Jehoshaphat and his people \Nhad no success. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.00,0:39:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now, \Nsometimes we think, of course, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.57,0:39:17.34,Default,,0,0,0,,that these kinds of situations \Nonly happened in Bible times. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.34,0:39:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But it’s amazing to see \Nhow our brothers in our modern day \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.68,0:39:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,have had that same kind of faith \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.74,0:39:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and have stood firm against the lion. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.08,0:39:29.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Here are just a couple of experiences \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.08,0:39:31.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that really touched my heart. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.52,0:39:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Here’s one about a brother \Nnamed Pavel from Russia. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.56,0:39:37.56,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1958, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.56,0:39:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Pavel was arrested for religious activities. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.83,0:39:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“Accompanying me to the train,” he says, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.30,0:39:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,“the officer [with me] said, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.53,0:39:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Look at your wife for the last time \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.34,0:39:51.21,Default,,0,0,0,,because you will never see her again.’” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.21,0:39:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, there’s the lion. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.34,0:39:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,“I spent six months \Nin solitary confinement before my trial. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.01,0:40:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,“During interrogations, . . . \Nthe investigators did everything \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.72,0:40:03.82,Default,,0,0,0,,“to undermine my faith. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.82,0:40:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,“Sometimes violence was used. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.39,0:40:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I begged Jehovah \Nto give me the strength to stay firm.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.39,0:40:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,But now look what happened. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.99,0:40:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,“During a routine interrogation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.70,0:40:20.77,Default,,0,0,0,,“the investigator called me \Ninto his study and [he] said: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.77,0:40:24.27,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Now we will show you \Nwhat your organization is doing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.27,0:40:27.61,Default,,0,0,0,,“Then you can see \Nif it is God’s work or not!’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.61,0:40:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,“Looking at me intently, he continued: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.91,0:40:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘This year your convention in New York \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.32,0:40:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘was attended by 253,000 people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.59,0:40:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘in two stadiums. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.59,0:40:42.69,Default,,0,0,0,,“The convention lasted eight days.’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.69,0:40:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“The investigator strewed \Nthe table with photographs. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.03,0:40:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,“In one of them, \NI saw happy delegates \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.83,0:40:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“in colorful native dress \Nembracing one another. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.07,0:40:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“Another photo showed \NBrother Knorr giving a talk, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.30,0:40:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“and yet others showed the baptism. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.34,0:41:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,“The investigator could not even imagine \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.54,0:41:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,“what I was feeling at that moment. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.75,0:41:07.41,Default,,0,0,0,,“I felt that I was attending the convention \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.41,0:41:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,“without ever having left the prison. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.25,0:41:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,“I felt new strength flooding into me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.99,0:41:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,“[It was just what] I had needed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.06,0:41:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,“. . . And Jehovah generously \Nblessed me in a special way. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.26,0:41:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I was ready to endure further.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.00,0:41:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn’t that amazing?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.00,0:41:28.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Here’s another similar experience, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.24,0:41:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,1960, also in Russia, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.97,0:41:34.48,Default,,0,0,0,,a large publicized trial \Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.48,0:41:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,About 300 persons \Nwere present in the courtroom, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.65,0:41:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,including many of our brothers and sisters. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.81,0:41:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, as the evidence—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.82,0:41:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,As evidence against the brothers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.95,0:41:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the prosecutor decided to present \Na letter from Nathan H. Knorr. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.96,0:41:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the brothers \Nwho attended the trial said this: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.49,0:41:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,“The prosecutor loudly began to read a letter \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.86,0:41:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,“that had been intercepted by the KGB \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.47,0:42:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,“from Brother Knorr \Nto the brothers in the Soviet Union. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.87,0:42:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,“For all of us Witnesses present in the hall, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.07,0:42:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“it was a wonderful gift from Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.78,0:42:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,“This letter warmed our hearts! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.15,0:42:13.88,Default,,0,0,0,,“We heard wise counsel from the Bible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.88,0:42:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,“and encouragement to serve \Nour fellow believers lovingly \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.35,0:42:20.49,Default,,0,0,0,,“and to stay faithful [even] under trials. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.49,0:42:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,“The prosecutor read the letter \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.96,0:42:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,“from the beginning to the very end. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.86,0:42:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,“We listened with rapt attention. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.53,0:42:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It seemed to us that we were \Nattending a convention!”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.80,0:42:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now, brothers, what additional lessons \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.97,0:42:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,do we learn from these two experiences? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.57,0:42:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,When we stand our ground against Satan, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.38,0:42:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,firm in the faith, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.38,0:42:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,then Jehovah will do just what he promised \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.28,0:42:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,at 1 Peter 5:10. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.19,0:42:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you see what it says there? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.32,0:42:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,“But after you have suffered a little while, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.66,0:43:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,“the God of all undeserved kindness, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:00.53,0:43:04.30,Default,,0,0,0,,“who called you to his everlasting glory \Nin union with Christ, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.30,0:43:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,“will himself finish your training. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.60,0:43:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,“He will make you firm, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.60,0:43:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,“he will make you strong, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.71,0:43:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,he will firmly ground you.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.64,0:43:16.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So, brothers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.64,0:43:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,can we survive the attack of a roaring lion? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.91,0:43:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.92,0:43:26.99,Default,,0,0,0,,With firm faith, let’s stand fast \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.99,0:43:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and see the salvation from Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.46,0:43:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Firm faith is needed to resist \Nthe relentless attacks of Satan the Devil. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.43,0:43:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The modern-day examples brought out \Nin the presentation are truly inspiring. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.10,0:43:45.21,Default,,0,0,0,,However, \Ndid you notice that Brother Sanderson \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.21,0:43:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,also applied \Nthe Biblical example of Jehoshaphat? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.54,0:43:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The Bible is full of accounts that can revive \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.81,0:43:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and renew our courage \Nevery time we read them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.12,0:43:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But here’s a question: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.29,0:44:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,When should we develop the type of faith \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.29,0:44:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,that can resist the attack \Nof “a roaring lion”? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.16,0:44:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it something \Nonly longtime servants of Jehovah can do? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.73,0:44:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Ecclesiastes 12:1 says \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.00,0:44:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to “remember, then, your Grand Creator \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.00,0:44:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,in the days of your youth.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.47,0:44:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Young ones, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.47,0:44:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,do you find it a challenge \Nto read the Bible every day? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.21,0:44:27.01,Default,,0,0,0,,A few of your peers \Nhave excellent suggestions \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.01,0:44:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,based on how they do their Bible reading \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.32,0:44:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and how they get the most benefit from it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.59,0:44:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I often put it off until later. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.82,0:44:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,So I come home in the evening tired, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.99,0:44:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and I like to relax. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.09,0:44:41.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, very often, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.33,0:44:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I was tired for many different reasons, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.00,0:44:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and that is why I didn’t have the motivation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.10,0:44:47.10,Default,,0,0,0,,even to start Bible reading \Nin the first place. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.10,0:44:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I also had many phases \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.54,0:44:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,where it was really tough \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.07,0:44:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,to stick it out with Bible reading. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.34,0:44:55.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially in the age of social media, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.61,0:44:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,there are many other things \Nyou can fill your day with. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.68,0:45:01.98,Default,,0,0,0,,One hobby that mainly got in the way \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.98,0:45:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,was watching movies. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.98,0:45:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I really spent a lot of time on that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.45,0:45:10.46,Default,,0,0,0,,This often steals precious time \Nyou could have made better use of. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:10.46,0:45:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So something that moved me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.69,0:45:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,was the thought that through Bible reading, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.80,0:45:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,you’re actually talking with Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.80,0:45:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You pray to him, and he \Nis then answering you through the Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.17,0:45:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,As Jehovah promised, he can give us \Nboth the power and the desire to act. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.51,0:45:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I just pray to Jehovah, please, \Nto first give me the power to read \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.71,0:45:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and then the desire follows. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.08,0:45:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I decided \Nto simply start and stick with it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.58,0:45:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I started with reading my favorite book, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.72,0:45:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and that way it was easier for me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.92,0:45:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I started with Genesis \Njust to get through the whole Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.03,0:45:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,My favorite Bible book is Esther. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.03,0:45:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And because I think \Nshe was a very special person, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.20,0:45:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,it was especially then that I could imagine \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.57,0:45:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,what her situation was like \Nand what kind of a person she was \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.27,0:46:02.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and I could see myself in the account. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:02.54,0:46:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The weekly Bible reading program \Nhas been such a guideline. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.61,0:46:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s motivating since we discuss \Nthis content at the meetings, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.95,0:46:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and I could use the study aids \Nin our workbook too. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.89,0:46:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You can better relate \Nto the brothers’ and sisters’ comments \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.56,0:46:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,because you’ve read the material yourself, \Nand I can comment too. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.06,0:46:22.86,Default,,0,0,0,,When I’m reading the Bible \Nin the JW Library app on my phone, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.86,0:46:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,there is, of course, \Nthe risk that it vibrates, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.13,0:46:27.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and I get a message. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.13,0:46:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, of course, you have the urge \Nto check to see who just wrote me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.54,0:46:33.41,Default,,0,0,0,,For me personally, then, it’s really helpful \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:33.41,0:46:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,when I put my phone in airplane mode \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.44,0:46:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,so that I can really focus \Non what I’m reading \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.71,0:46:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and nothing can distract me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.75,0:46:45.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I like reading at home, \Nbut I also like to do it outdoors \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.65,0:46:49.12,Default,,0,0,0,,because I think that’s \Nwhere you’re closest to Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.12,0:46:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I never just read about the events \Nthat are described in the Bible, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.89,0:46:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,but I ask myself questions like: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.90,0:46:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,‘Why did Jehovah have this written down? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.00,0:46:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What is in there for me personally?’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.13,0:47:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,This helps me to stay focused \Nand not just scratch the surface; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.84,0:47:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,otherwise, my mind \Nwould immediately start wandering. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.64,0:47:09.18,Default,,0,0,0,,At a convention, \NI learned something that helps me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.18,0:47:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to really take in the things I read. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.41,0:47:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The point discussed \Nwas to remember to look \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.45,0:47:17.45,Default,,0,0,0,,in four different directions \Nwhen meditating, so to speak. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.45,0:47:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,First, look upwards \Nto find out exactly what I am learning \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:21.86,0:47:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,from the text about Jehovah; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.02,0:47:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,then downwards to find out \Nwhat it teaches me about his purpose, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.00,0:47:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,about what he wants for the earth; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.50,0:47:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,then look at myself, \Nhow I can personally benefit now; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.10,0:47:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,and eventually towards others, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.37,0:47:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,thinking about how I can help other people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.54,0:47:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,with this particular Bible text. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.98,0:47:48.98,Default,,0,0,0,,In the JW Library app, there are \Nfour different colors for highlighting text, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.98,0:47:53.15,Default,,0,0,0,,so I simply use a different color \Nfor each of the four directions \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.15,0:47:57.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and highlight them \Non my tablet or smartphone. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:57.69,0:48:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, one of my hobbies is drawing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.16,0:48:03.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I decided, one time, \Nthat I was going to draw \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.90,0:48:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the spiritual suit of armor, \Nall of its different parts \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.50,0:48:08.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and their symbolic meanings. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.50,0:48:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And this especially helped me \Nto actually see the benefit of it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.71,0:48:15.41,Default,,0,0,0,,to see how many wonderful resources \NJehovah provides us with \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.41,0:48:18.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and that he never leaves us alone. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.08,0:48:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Another thing \NI like very much is the category \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.98,0:48:23.65,Default,,0,0,0,,“Bible Study Activities” \Nwhere you can directly pick a topic \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.65,0:48:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that you personally find interesting \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.65,0:48:27.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and then read that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.49,0:48:28.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s Jehovah’s Word. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.92,0:48:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I love him and also want \Nto please him, of course. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.19,0:48:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s why it’s very important \Nto understand his Word. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.93,0:48:37.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It feels really good when you’ve understood \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.16,0:48:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,a difficult phrase by doing it this way. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.50,0:48:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It actually makes you feel \Nlike you’ve achieved something, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.37,0:48:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and this brings you a lot closer to Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.87,0:48:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It happens often that you don’t even know \Nwhat you should pray about \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.84,0:48:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,or what you could thank Jehovah for. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.28,0:48:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,My personal Bible reading \Nhas helped me with this a lot \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.68,0:48:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,because now I know exactly \Nwhat I want to tell Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.55,0:49:02.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Daily Bible reading is very important to me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.29,0:49:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,as it gives me some sort \Nof inner balance when I face situations \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.26,0:49:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that may be unfamiliar or shake me up. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.76,0:49:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I know that no matter what the problem is,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.03,0:49:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah always has the right answer prepared.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.94,0:49:17.37,Default,,0,0,0,,At the beginning, it is really hard. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.37,0:49:20.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to fight to keep it up, \Nand you definitely need discipline. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.97,0:49:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But after a while, \Nyou truly start to enjoy it \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.08,0:49:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,and it gets easier and easier \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.08,0:49:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and you’re happy \Nthat you started in the first place. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.42,0:49:33.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I really think that when Jehovah sees \Nhow much effort you put into it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.09,0:49:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,he is genuinely proud of you, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.42,0:49:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and that’s the best thing \Nthat can happen to you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.17,0:49:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,These young brothers and sisters \Ndidn’t just acquire knowledge; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.97,0:49:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,they drew closer to Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.47,0:49:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,This will help them build \Na fine foundation for their future, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.28,0:49:59.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can too. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.41,0:50:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It may not be easy at first, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.65,0:50:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,but as one young brother suggested, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.98,0:50:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,start with something \Nthat captures your interest. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.69,0:50:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Try using the JW Library app \Nor a handy notebook \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.56,0:50:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,to keep track of points you hope \Nto apply or discuss at family worship. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.10,0:50:17.70,Default,,0,0,0,,This will make it \Na part of your daily routine \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.70,0:50:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,that you look forward to. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.67,0:50:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Each segment \Nin the program has highlighted \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.10,0:50:26.74,Default,,0,0,0,,some way we can build \Na strong relationship with God. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.74,0:50:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Our music video depicts the joy of marriage, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.51,0:50:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,where Jehovah is part of a threefold cord \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.88,0:50:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,—one that cannot quickly be torn apart. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.05,0:50:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The song is called “Truly in Love.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.70,0:51:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a gift that comes from above,\NA lovely gift called being in love.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:03.08,0:51:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When two hearts begin to beat as one,\NThen a wonderful time has begun.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.93,0:51:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s simple, so easy.\NAnd it’s something we know.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.33,0:51:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,With a threefold cord,\NLove will grow.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.84,0:51:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,With Jehovah to guide us in all that we do,\NHow I love to be truly in love\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.82,0:51:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,With someone like you,\NSomeone like you.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.00,0:52:07.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Trials will come our way,\NBut our love will grow stronger each day.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.21,0:52:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,We will build a bond that no one can break.\NWe will build a love that no one will take.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.85,0:52:23.16,Default,,0,0,0,,No, no, no one, no.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.16,0:52:28.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s simple, so easy.\NAnd it’s something we know.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.66,0:52:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,With a threefold cord,\NLove will grow.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.60,0:52:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,With Jehovah to guide us in all that we do,\NHow I love to be truly in love\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.81,0:52:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,With someone like you,\NSomeone like you.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.56,0:53:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing can destroy our love.\NThis precious gift is from our God up above.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.54,0:53:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Exclusive devotion​\N—‘love’s as strong as death.’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.18,0:53:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You are “bone of my bones”; \Nyou are “flesh of my flesh,”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.18,0:53:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Such an excellent woman in all that you do.\NI will spend all my life loving you.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.90,0:53:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to know how I feel\N’Cause my love for you is so very real.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.91,0:54:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I bless the day you came into my life.\NI bless the day I made you my wife.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.82,0:54:05.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I do.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.96,0:54:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s simple, so easy.\NAnd it’s something we know.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:12.00,0:54:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,With a threefold cord,\NLove will grow.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:17.67,0:54:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,With Jehovah to guide us in all that we do,\NHow I love to be truly in love\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.78,0:54:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,With someone like you,\NSomeone like you.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.43,0:54:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,How I love to be truly in love\NWith someone like you.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:57.44,0:55:02.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So many of our brothers and sisters \Ncan agree with the words of that song: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.45,0:55:07.82,Default,,0,0,0,,“With a threefold cord, love will grow.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.82,0:55:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,In marriage, in youth, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.99,0:55:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,really, in all things we’ve considered, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.39,0:55:16.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah will be there to guide us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.30,0:55:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What will be the result? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.37,0:55:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ll find the warmth and security \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.07,0:55:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,of being securely wrapped \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.37,0:55:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,in Jehovah’s “bag of life.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.91,0:55:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,We hope you enjoyed our program. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.24,0:55:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We conclude by heading \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.74,0:55:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,to the beautiful tropical island \Nof Sri Lanka, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.61,0:55:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,off the southeast coast \Nof India in the Indian Ocean. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.22,0:55:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 6,000 publishers \Nmake up the 112 congregations on the island, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.82,0:55:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,including 13 isolated groups. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.86,0:55:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,As you travel throughout the country, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.16,0:55:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the scars of the decades-long civil war \Nare still evident. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:52.00,0:55:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,However, our brothers and sisters display \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.14,0:55:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the beautiful spirit of Christian unity. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.14,0:56:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Publishers preach the good news \Nto those on the coast, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.17,0:56:03.18,Default,,0,0,0,,high in the mountains, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.18,0:56:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and in the bustling cities. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.21,0:56:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,More than 8,000 Bible studies \Nare being conducted, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.05,0:56:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and over 650 brothers and sisters \Nare in the pioneer work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.05,0:56:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the dense population \Nin the city of Colombo, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.92,0:56:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,those in metropolitan witnessing \Nsee an average of almost 17,000 people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.93,0:56:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in just one 8-hour period. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.47,0:56:27.80,Default,,0,0,0,,High in Sri Lanka’s tea mountains \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.80,0:56:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,is a small congregation \Nin the town of Badulla. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.14,0:56:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Their productive ministry takes them \Ninto banana plantations, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.38,0:56:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,jungles, and mountain tea estates \Nas they search \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.81,0:56:41.65,Default,,0,0,0,,for those receptive to the good news. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.65,0:56:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Despite differing ethnic backgrounds, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.48,0:56:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,they’re completely united \Nin worship and brotherly affection. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.29,0:56:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Our brothers and sisters \Nwho are wrapped up \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.76,0:56:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,in Jehovah’s “bag of life” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.76,0:56:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,send you their warm love and greetings \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.76,0:56:56.93,Default,,0,0,0,,from the mountaintops of Sri Lanka! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.93,0:56:59.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for watching. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.03,0:57:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,From the world headquarters \Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.70,0:57:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,this is JW Broadcasting. \N
